{
  "texts": [
    "Physically, when the net effective coupling of slow modes to all dissipators cancels (for symmetry reasons) or when the slow mode is supported on subspaces orthogonal to the dissipators, κ can vanish or be numerically extremely small [3,17].",
    "Uniform placement avoids such cancellations by construction and therefore yields robust gaps.The rapid suppression of κ with λ for one-site/two-site dissipation implies very long relaxation times in the localized regime, which is a practical concern if one aims to prepare steady states experimentally (coherence times, experimental drifts).",
    "Conversely, the strong sensitivity of κ to λ and to placement suggests the rapidity can serve as a compact diagnostic of localization and transport crossovers in engineered open systems.",
    "The influence of t N suggests possible control knobs to tune relaxation times: increasing long-range coupling enhances coupling to dissipators and speeds relaxation.",
    "V. CONCLUSIONSWe used third-quantization to study Liouvillian rapidities of a helical quasiperiodic fermionic chain subject to engineered linear dissipation."
  ]
}